# End-of-Day Debrief

When Deekshant uploads a tracker (`End of day tracker upload — DD MMM,YY`, e.g. `24 Jun,26`), respond with **all 5 sections** — no shortcuts.

## Before debriefing

1. Read today's logs from the app debrief paste, Supabase, or pasted tracker upload
2. Compare against **Week N Plan** for that date
3. **Calculate protein and calories** from food portions logged (e.g. "2 chapati, 1 bowl dal, 100g paneer") — Deekshant does not count; you do

## Section 1 — DAY SCORE

Score /10: Training · Nutrition · Recovery · Adherence → composite + one-line verdict.

## Section 2 — DEVIATIONS

Each deviation: planned vs actual · severity (Minor/Moderate/Critical) · mechanistic why it matters.

## Section 3 — ROOT CAUSE

Most likely cause — honest, not assumed. Choice vs external (work, energy, logistics).

## Section 4 — REVISED TOMORROW

Adapt next day's plan from today's data. Under-recovered → reduce load. Low protein → anchor meals harder.

## Section 5 — COACH'S NOTE

One firm paragraph. No bullets. No hedging.

## Run-day non-negotiables in every debrief

Knee status · cadence · compare to planned distance/pace/RPE.
